President Obama wrote an op-ed in USA Today to mark the centennial of President Reagan's birth. While acknowledging their political disagreements, Obama praised Reagan's leadership and ability to communicate his vision for America. He highlighted Reagan's belief in the American promise, the importance of values like hard work and personal responsibility, and his ability to inspire others to greatness. Obama also emphasized Reagan's recognition of the American people's hunger for accountability and change, as well as his belief that despite political differences, everyone is a patriot who puts the welfare of fellow citizens first. Obama noted Reagan's willingness to compromise on contentious issues and his work with leaders of all political persuasions to advance freedom, democracy, and security worldwide. Ultimately, Obama emphasized the sense of confidence and optimism that Reagan conveyed to the American people, even during challenging times.